"Excuse me... I hate to interrupt, but could I borrow Makoto
for a moment?"

"What's the rush? Makoto-sama is currently speaking with
us..."

"...It's rare for Mamoru to approach me. It seems like it's
something important. Sorry everyone, I'll be stepping away
for a bit."

As Golden Week came to an end, so did Suzuki's suspension.
Since then, Suzuki has become quite chatty with Makoto, and
now even his entourage seems to have warmed up to him.

There's no doubt in my mind that Suzuki must have done
something terrible to Makoto. Yet now, he seems to be closer
to her than I am. I just couldn't stand it, and it was very
painful to watch.

Eventually, I couldn't bear the sight any longer and quit
school. To avoid getting hurt, I shut myself away in a dimly
lit room and began to spend my days in a daze.

By the way, I heard there was an arson incident at the
school I used to attend. Apparently, the behavior of one of
the female students has been getting stranger by the day.
But since I quit school, it's none of my business anymore.
